
[1]incandescence

   INCANDES'CENCE, n. [L. incandescens, incandesco; in and candesco;
   candeo, caneo, to be white, to shine; canus, white.]

   A white heat; or the glowing whiteness of a body caused by intense
   heat. We say, a metal is heated to incandescence.
